Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.08,0:00:07.03,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Previously on Reacher...{\r}\N{\rEng}《神探雷彻》前情提要
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.23,0:00:10.03,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, whatever your friends were involved in was big enough to get them killed.{\r}\N{\rEng}不管你朋友卷入的是什么事 其金额都大到害死了他们
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.23,0:00:12.95,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way the Tony Swan I recruited is a part of this.{\r}\N{\rEng}我招募的托尼斯旺 绝对不可能参与此事
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.15,0:00:16.54,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems Swan's title was assistant director of security.{\r}\N{\rEng}看来斯旺的职位是安全总监助理
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.74,0:00:19.66,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,"Shane Langston. Director of Security."{\r}\N{\rEng}“谢恩兰斯顿 安全总监”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.86,0:00:21.92,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he's the guy I got on the phone in Atlantic City.{\r}\N{\rEng}也许在大西洋城 跟我通话的就是这个人
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.12,0:00:23.21,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to talk to Malcolm Lavoy.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们得跟马尔科姆拉沃伊谈谈
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.41,0:00:24.79,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll never get close enough to a senator{\r}\N{\rEng}我们永远没法接近参议员
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.99,0:00:26.21,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,to find out what he may or may not know.{\r}\N{\rEng}从他口中套话
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.41,0:00:27.42,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, we don't need to.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们不需要接近他
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.62,0:00:28.88,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Daniel Boyd,{\r}\N{\rEng}丹尼尔博伊德
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.08,0:00:30.05,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Senator Lavoy's legislative director.{\r}\N{\rEng}拉沃伊参议员的立法主任
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.25,0:00:33.22,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Little Wing can knock anything out of the sky.{\r}\N{\rEng}小翅膀可以击中空中的任何物体
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.42,0:00:34.39,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,New Age has two bases.{\r}\N{\rEng}新时代有两个基地
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.59,0:00:36.18,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Software made in New York{\r}\N{\rEng}软件是在纽约开发的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.38,0:00:38.31,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,hardware at a manufacturing plant in Denver.{\r}\N{\rEng}硬件是在丹佛的制造工厂制造的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.51,0:00:39.52,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,What are our directives?{\r}\N{\rEng}我们的指令是什么?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.72,0:00:40.81,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You and Dixon go to Denver.{\r}\N{\rEng}你和迪克森去丹佛
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.01,0:00:42.85,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,O'Donnell and I will head down to D.C.{\r}\N{\rEng}奥唐纳和我会去华盛顿特区
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.05,0:00:45.57,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Want to swing by Homeland, see what they know about A.M.{\r}\N{\rEng}我想去国土安全局 看看他们是否知道AM的事
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.76,0:00:46.87,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Saddle up...{\r}\N{\rEng}给马备好鞍
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.04,0:00:50.38,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,...'cause we're about to do a whole lot of cowboy shit.{\r}\N{\rEng}因为我们要去做一大堆牛仔的事
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.27,0:00:57.08,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye!Quit it!{\r}\N{\rEng}再见!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.63,0:01:01.62,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit it!{\r}\N{\rEng}别闹了!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.82,0:01:03.67,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna get you!{\r}\N{\rEng}我会抓住你的!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.87,0:01:05.08,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,-  No, you're not. - Don't drop my teddy ever again{\r}\N{\rEng}不 你抓不到的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.28,0:01:09.15,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,or I will...  ...at your face.{\r}\N{\rEng}别再丢我的泰迪熊了 否则我会…你的脸!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.07,0:01:12.97,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!{\r}\N{\rEng}住手!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.17,0:01:15.01,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh.{\r}\N{\rEng}你带肾上腺素笔了吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.21,0:01:16.64,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- You got the EpiPens? - Yes, of course.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 当然带了 - 伍比呢?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.84,0:01:18.51,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- And woobie? - Woobie, Panda-pal{\r}\N{\rEng}伍比毯、熊猫朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.71,0:01:19.77,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Lindsay the Monkey, they're all packed.{\r}\N{\rEng}猴子林赛 全都装好了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.97,0:01:21.06,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Grab the burner phone.{\r}\N{\rEng}带上一次性手机
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.26,0:01:22.48,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,No contact with anyone. Not your parents{\r}\N{\rEng}别跟任何人联系 不要找你父母
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.68,0:01:23.94,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and definitely not your sister.{\r}\N{\rEng}而且千万别联系你姐姐
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.14,0:01:25.35,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,She puts everything on Facebook.{\r}\N{\rEng}她什么都往脸书上发
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.55,0:01:26.86,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- I know the drill.{\r}\N{\rEng}我知道这一套
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.06,0:01:28.90,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Go to Asheville. Take the boys. Plenty for you to do there.{\r}\N{\rEng}去阿什维尔 带男孩们过去 那里有很多事做
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.10,0:01:30.32,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,It's touristy. You'll blend in.{\r}\N{\rEng}那是旅游胜地 你会融入其中
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.52,0:01:32.80,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Use cash and this pay-as-you-go credit card.{\r}\N{\rEng}用现金和现收现付信用卡
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.94,0:01:34.82,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Scale of one to ten, how bad is this?{\r}\N{\rEng}按从一到十打分 情况有多糟?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.02,0:01:36.66,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,They're not gonna come after you.{\r}\N{\rEng}他们不会去找你们的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.86,0:01:38.95,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We're just playing it safe. Belts and suspenders.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们只是谨慎行事 额外小心
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.15,0:01:40.76,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,One to ten.{\r}\N{\rEng}按从一到十打分
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.51,0:01:44.75,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,For you guys? Four, tops.{\r}\N{\rEng}对于你们来说 最多四分
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.95,0:01:46.33,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,How about you?{\r}\N{\rEng}那你呢?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.53,0:01:48.71,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we're dealing with some pretty bad guys, but...{\r}\N{\rEng}我们正在处理一些相当坏的家伙
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.91,0:01:50.55,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I got the gang with me. We'll be fine.{\r}\N{\rEng}但我有朋友在身边 我们会没事的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.75,0:01:52.47,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be over in a couple of days, promise.{\r}\N{\rEng}过几天就结束了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.66,0:01:56.86,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I got to get the baby ready.{\r}\N{\rEng}我得让孩子做好准备 就像上次一样
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.49,0:02:00.72,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Give my tie back!{\r}\N{\rEng}把我的泰迪熊还给我!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.92,0:02:03.02,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- I need... - She doesn't panic.{\r}\N{\rEng}我需要你们去…她并不惊慌
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.18,0:02:06.04,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Accepts reality on reality's terms.{\r}\N{\rEng}…去挑你们的衣服 既来之 则安之
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.18,0:02:08.69,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Daughter of an ER nurse, Chicago fire chief.{\r}\N{\rEng}她是急诊室护士 和芝加哥消防队长的女儿
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.89,0:02:12.19,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Tough as they come. - Beautiful, tough, smart.{\r}\N{\rEng}非常坚强\N漂亮、坚强、聪明
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.39,0:02:13.40,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,She lose a bet?{\r}\N{\rEng}她打赌输了才嫁给你的?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.60,0:02:16.32,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,...dinner. That's what I'm making.{\r}\N{\rEng}这就是我在做的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.52,0:02:17.74,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,If someone asked me back in the day{\r}\N{\rEng}如果当初有人问我
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.94,0:02:19.62,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,where I thought you'd wind up{\r}\N{\rEng}你的结局会是怎样
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.82,0:02:21.58,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd have predicted a slow death from gonorrhea{\r}\N{\rEng}我会预测你因为淋病慢慢死去
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.78,0:02:24.33,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and a half dozen girlfriends fighting over an '04 Miata.{\r}\N{\rEng}还会有六个女朋友 为了一辆04年的马自达大打出手
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.53,0:02:26.37,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well, turns out I didn't want{\r}\N{\rEng}是啊 原来我并不想要
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.57,0:02:29.21,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,every girl in the world, just the right one.{\r}\N{\rEng}世界上的每一个女孩 只想要对的那个
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.56,0:02:33.11,Mark,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to calm down a little?{\r}\N{\rEng}你想稍微冷静一下吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.73,0:02:36.59,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Neagley and Dixon just got to the Denver plant.{\r}\N{\rEng}内格利和迪克森刚到丹佛的工厂
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.79,0:02:38.59,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. Maybe they get ahold of those missiles{\r}\N{\rEng}很好 她们也许能拿到那些导弹
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.79,0:02:40.97,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and your family won't have to be gone long.{\r}\N{\rEng}你的家人就不必离开太久
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.16,0:02:43.66,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a slowpoke.{\r}\N{\rEng}你真慢
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.93,0:02:48.66,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.{\r}\N{\rEng}好的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.29,0:02:56.28,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,A few days wouldn't hurt.You'll never get me.{\r}\N{\rEng}离开几天没关系
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.48,0:02:57.84,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I will.{\r}\N{\rEng}我会的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.94,0:03:00.84,Mark,,0000,0000,0000,,科罗拉多州丹佛
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.97,0:03:05.00,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,The DCMA was here a month ago.{\r}\N{\rEng}国防合约管理局一个月前来过这里
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.20,0:03:06.96,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, and now we're back.{\r}\N{\rEng}是啊 现在我们又回来了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.16,0:03:09.63,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the cold sores of government oversight.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们可是政府监管的“疱疹” 总是神出鬼没
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.83,0:03:12.19,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if you please? Your foreman?{\r}\N{\rEng}现在 请把你们的领班叫来
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.29,0:03:13.71,Mark,,0000,0000,0000,,新时代科技 配送仓库
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.91,0:03:14.73,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait here.{\r}\N{\rEng}在这里等着
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.86,0:03:20.34,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Never ceases to amaze me how far you can get into a place{\r}\N{\rEng}真是让我惊叹不已 你拿着写字板 表现自然
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.54,0:03:24.10,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,if you just act like you're supposed to be there and carry a clipboard.{\r}\N{\rEng}就好像你就应该在那儿一样
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.33,0:03:29.69,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- How you feeling?{\r}\N{\rEng}你觉得怎么样?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.89,0:03:31.36,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Sore.{\r}\N{\rEng}疼
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.56,0:03:34.11,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, fighting in heels takes some getting used to.{\r}\N{\rEng}穿着高跟鞋打架 是需要一段时间适应的
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.31,0:03:36.49,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Walking in heels takes some getting used to.{\r}\N{\rEng}穿高跟鞋走路 也需要一段时间适应
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.69,0:03:38.49,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Never wore 'em.{\r}\N{\rEng}我从来没穿过
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.69,0:03:41.45,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- You never wore heels? - Nope.{\r}\N{\rEng}你之前从来不穿高跟鞋?\N不穿
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.65,0:03:44.74,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Not even to a school dance? - Never went to one.{\r}\N{\rEng}连学校舞会上都不穿?\N从没去过
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.94,0:03:48.43,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,When I wasn't studying or taking care of my dad, I had to work.{\r}\N{\rEng}我不学习 或者不照顾我爸的时候 我得去工作
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.93,0:03:52.08,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, bad music, warm punch{\r}\N{\rEng}也就是糟糕的音乐、温暖的酒水
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.28,0:03:54.09,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and some clammy hands feeling you up...{\r}\N{\rEng}以及一些摸着你的黏糊糊的手
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.29,0:03:56.06,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,you didn't miss much.{\r}\N{\rEng}你并没有错过太多
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.57,0:04:03.26,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody told me about this.{\r}\N{\rEng}没人跟我说你们要来检查
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.46,0:04:06.39,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't be a surprise inspection if we called ahead.{\r}\N{\rEng}如果我们提前通知就不是突击检查了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.59,0:04:09.23,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle Sam wants to make sure you're using his money wisely.{\r}\N{\rEng}山姆大叔想确定 你们把钱用在了正道上
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.43,0:04:10.85,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,So we're here to take a look at Little Wing shoulder-fired launchers{\r}\N{\rEng}所以我们来看看小翅膀肩扛式发射器
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.05,0:04:15.78,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and missiles.The specs, the manufacturing protocols{\r}\N{\rEng}以及导弹 检查它们的规格和制造协议
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.97,0:04:18.65,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,the order and delivery schedules...{\r}\N{\rEng}订单以及交货时间表
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.85,0:04:20.25,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Delivery schedule?{\r}\N{\rEng}交货时间表?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.19,0:04:23.45,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten minutes ago. That's the delivery schedule.{\r}\N{\rEng}交货时间就在十分钟前!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.65,0:04:25.74,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,The whole lot just went out the door.{\r}\N{\rEng}所有货物刚运出去
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.94,0:04:28.45,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,All 650 of them.{\r}\N{\rEng}总共650个
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.65,0:04:32.25,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- 650? - Here's the paperwork.{\r}\N{\rEng}650?这是相关文件
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.45,0:04:36.27,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,If someone had called me first, I'd have held them for you.{\r}\N{\rEng}如果有人先给我打电话 我本可以推迟交货 给你们留着
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.11,0:04:42.28,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Shit. - Yeah.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 糟了 - 是啊
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.06,0:05:15.92,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, there. You need an extra set of hands?{\r}\N{\rEng}嘿\N你需要帮忙吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.12,0:05:17.34,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,What I need{\r}\N{\rEng}我需要的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.54,0:05:18.98,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,is your truck.{\r}\N{\rEng}是你的卡车
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.14,0:05:53.26,Mark,,0000,0000,0000,,爆炸枪弹
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.94,0:06:03.73,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in business.{\r}\N{\rEng}一切按计划进行中
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.61,0:06:12.32,Mark,,0000,0000,0000,,匿名来电
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.41,0:06:14.85,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me good news.{\r}\N{\rEng}告诉我好消息吧
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.05,0:06:16.52,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,GPS tracker did the job.{\r}\N{\rEng}GPS追踪器完成了其使命
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.72,0:06:18.73,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Your associates at New Age came through.{\r}\N{\rEng}你在新时代的同事们还不错
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.93,0:06:21.28,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,They might be upset I killed the driver, though.{\r}\N{\rEng}但是我杀了司机 他们可能会伤心
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.47,0:06:23.53,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, they won't care so long as they get paid.{\r}\N{\rEng}只要他们能拿到钱就不会在意
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.73,0:06:26.57,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Never underestimate the power of greed.{\r}\N{\rEng}永远不要低估贪婪的力量
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.77,0:06:28.37,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Switch the trailers and get on the road.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 换车上路吧 - 好的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.57,0:06:31.05,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Will do. Meet you in New York.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们纽约见
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.60,0:06:35.46,Mark,,0000,0000,0000,,阿扎里马哈茂德
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.66,0:06:36.52,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,This name, right here...{\r}\N{\rEng}这里这个名字
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.64,0:06:38.85,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,...Azhari Mahmoud.{\r}\N{\rEng}阿扎里马哈茂德
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.44,0:06:44.05,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,So, the Aaron Miklos we were chasing down in Denver{\r}\N{\rEng}所以我们在丹佛 追捕的那个阿伦米克洛斯
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.25,0:06:45.67,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,that was Mahmoud?{\r}\N{\rEng}就是马哈茂德?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.87,0:06:47.59,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we've been calling him "A.M."{\r}\N{\rEng}是的 我们一直叫他“AM”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.79,0:06:50.76,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Guy's smart. Never been caught, no photos.{\r}\N{\rEng}这家伙很聪明 从未被捕 也没有照片
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.96,0:06:54.64,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell, we're not even sure what nationality he is.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们甚至都不确定他的国籍
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.84,0:06:56.14,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,From the little bit we know of him{\r}\N{\rEng}从我们对他仅有的了解来看
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.34,0:06:58.19,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,he can supposedly pass for Central American{\r}\N{\rEng}他可以伪装成中美洲人
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.39,0:07:00.48,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Italian, Greek, Middle Eastern.{\r}\N{\rEng}意大利人、希腊人、中东人…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.68,0:07:02.02,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a ghost.{\r}\N{\rEng}他如幽灵一般
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.22,0:07:04.78,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We have three short, innocuous recordings of him.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们有三段他的 简短且无关痛痒的录音
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.98,0:07:07.32,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Audio forensics matched it as the same guy.{\r}\N{\rEng}音频鉴定部证实是同一个人
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.52,0:07:09.28,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Each time, he's using a different identity.{\r}\N{\rEng}他每次都会使用不同的身份
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.48,0:07:10.66,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Ideology?{\r}\N{\rEng}意识形态呢?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.86,0:07:13.20,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,No political or religious affiliations.{\r}\N{\rEng}没有政治或宗教背景
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.40,0:07:14.75,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,His only god is money{\r}\N{\rEng}对他而言 唯有金钱才是上帝
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.95,0:07:16.41,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and he works for the highest bidder.{\r}\N{\rEng}他为出价最高的人工作
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.61,0:07:20.84,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,He hooks up bad actors with the tools they need for bad actions.{\r}\N{\rEng}他会接洽坏人 为他们提供做坏事所需的工具
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.03,0:07:23.30,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,First popped up on our radar six years ago.{\r}\N{\rEng}他在六年前第一次 出现在我们的视线中
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.50,0:07:26.67,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Terrorist cell caught trying to acquire tanks of experimental nerve gas.{\r}\N{\rEng}在恐怖分子试图 获取实验神经毒气罐的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.87,0:07:28.72,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We scooped up the whole lot.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们逮捕了整个团队
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.92,0:07:30.76,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,All of them except Mahmoud.{\r}\N{\rEng}所有人 除了马哈茂德
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.96,0:07:34.22,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Or whatever his name is.{\r}\N{\rEng}不管他叫什么
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.42,0:07:35.57,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Ghost.{\r}\N{\rEng}幽灵
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.24,0:07:40.15,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,This buy was supposed to happen with bearer bonds.{\r}\N{\rEng}这次购买本来应该用无记名债券
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.35,0:07:42.57,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, financial instrument of choice for tax evaders{\r}\N{\rEng}是的 逃税者、洗钱者
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.76,0:07:45.78,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,money launderers and other assorted assholes.{\r}\N{\rEng}和其他各种混蛋的 首选金融工具
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.98,0:07:48.36,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,The U.S. Treasury stopped issuing those in the '80s.{\r}\N{\rEng}美国财政部在80年代 就停止发行这些债券了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.56,0:07:51.16,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Some countries still use them. Those were from Luxembourg.{\r}\N{\rEng}有些国家仍在使用 那些是卢森堡的
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.36,0:07:54.16,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone as cautious as A.M. would use bearer bonds.{\r}\N{\rEng}像AM这么谨慎的人 会使用无记名债券
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.36,0:07:55.62,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,If issued in large enough amounts{\r}\N{\rEng}如果发行量足够大
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.82,0:07:58.08,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,you can carry an untraceable fortune in a briefcase.{\r}\N{\rEng}你可以用公文包 携带一笔无法追踪的财富
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.28,0:08:00.54,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- 65 million worth. - That's the problem.{\r}\N{\rEng}价值六千五百万 那就是问题所在
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.74,0:08:01.96,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You hold a bearer bond, that's like carrying{\r}\N{\rEng}你带着一张无记名债券
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.16,0:08:03.54,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,a million dollar bill.{\r}\N{\rEng}就像带着一百万美元的钞票
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.74,0:08:05.38,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,The bearer owns it.{\r}\N{\rEng}它归持有者所有
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.58,0:08:09.18,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,So no way A.M. lets anyone deliver payment but him.{\r}\N{\rEng}所以AM不可能 让除他以外的任何人运送酬劳
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.37,0:08:10.59,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,That's where he's vulnerable.{\r}\N{\rEng}这就是他的弱点
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.79,0:08:12.44,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like your brother.{\r}\N{\rEng}就像你哥哥一样
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.99,0:08:16.72,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Back when we worked the case, I asked Joe{\r}\N{\rEng}当年我们办案的时候 我问了乔
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.92,0:08:19.14,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,some questions of the financial side of things.{\r}\N{\rEng}一些财务方面的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.34,0:08:21.31,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,He said same thing you just did.{\r}\N{\rEng}他也是你这么说的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.51,0:08:23.90,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,A.M. will be the delivery boy. No one else.{\r}\N{\rEng}运送酬劳的会是AM 不会是其他人
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.10,0:08:25.82,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.We showed you ours.{\r}\N{\rEng}好的 我们给你们 看了我们掌握的信息
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.02,0:08:28.75,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's your turn.{\r}\N{\rEng}现在轮到你们了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.55,0:08:38.12,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We're still piecing it together, but, uh...{\r}\N{\rEng}我们还在整理中
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.32,0:08:40.96,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,we give you our word, when this bird's cooked{\r}\N{\rEng}但我们向你们保证 等时机成熟
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.16,0:08:42.58,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- we'll reach out. -  And you have my word{\r}\N{\rEng}- 我们会联系你们 - 我保证
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.78,0:08:44.92,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,we won't let this guy slip through our fingers again.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们不会再让这家伙 逃出我们的手掌心
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.12,0:08:46.75,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,A.M. and everyone working with him{\r}\N{\rEng}AM和他的所有同伙
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.95,0:08:49.48,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,will be prosecuted to the fullest extent of the law.{\r}\N{\rEng}都将受到法律的最大制裁
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.98,0:08:54.36,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless we kill them all first.{\r}\N{\rEng}除非我们先把他们都杀了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.41,0:09:00.62,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, guys.{\r}\N{\rEng}谢谢你们
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.54,0:09:08.54,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like his brother.{\r}\N{\rEng}跟他哥哥一样
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.09,0:09:12.09,Mark,,0000,0000,0000,,神探雷彻
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.07,0:09:41.31,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,18-wheelers can't go that fast on these roads.{\r}\N{\rEng}18轮车在这路上开不快的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.51,0:09:43.16,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got a decent shot at catching them.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们有机会赶上他们
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.29,0:09:50.00,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, especially if they come to a stop.{\r}\N{\rEng}是啊 尤其是他们中途停车了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.59,0:09:59.08,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are these guys?{\r}\N{\rEng}这些人是谁?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.28,0:10:00.49,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,They're the guys who are gonna tell us{\r}\N{\rEng}会告诉我们卡车坏了的人
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.69,0:10:02.04,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,the truck broke down and they had to call{\r}\N{\rEng}而且他们不得不 打电话
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.24,0:10:04.33,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,another one to come pick up the trailer.{\r}\N{\rEng}叫另一个人来取车
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.53,0:10:07.04,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,But no way a second truck got here before us.{\r}\N{\rEng}但第二辆卡车不可能 在我们之前赶到
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.24,0:10:10.05,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- No. - This is a hijacking.{\r}\N{\rEng}不\N这是劫车
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.33,0:10:13.72,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Any chance you're wrong?{\r}\N{\rEng}有没有可能你是错的?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.65,0:10:17.80,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not wrong!{\r}\N{\rEng}我没错
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.00,0:10:19.68,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,How the fuck did they know who we are?{\r}\N{\rEng}他们怎么知道我们是谁?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.88,0:10:22.87,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Foreman must've called New Age about two government inspectors.{\r}\N{\rEng}领班肯定给新时代打电话 说了两个政府检查员的事
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.07,0:10:25.74,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Langston finds out and calls these dickheads.{\r}\N{\rEng}兰斯顿发现后给这些混蛋打了电话
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.83,0:11:12.67,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,The fuck?{\r}\N{\rEng}什么鬼?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.36,0:11:40.09,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- I think we got him. - Yeah.{\r}\N{\rEng}我觉得我们干掉他了\N是啊
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.29,0:11:43.76,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Also looks like we got a front tire and gas tank.{\r}\N{\rEng}看来我们还打中了 一个前胎和一个油箱
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.09,0:11:48.56,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- We're not getting out of here. - No.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 我们离不开了 - 不 我去报警
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.76,0:11:50.90,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'll call the cops. - Make it anonymous.{\r}\N{\rEng}匿名报警
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.10,0:11:52.82,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Copy that. Do me a favor, grab the manifest.{\r}\N{\rEng}收到 帮我个忙 拿一下清单
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.01,0:11:55.50,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We need the license plate off of it.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们需要把车牌取下来
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.26,0:12:09.47,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, shit.{\r}\N{\rEng}天啊
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.56,0:12:13.84,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up, Neagley?{\r}\N{\rEng}怎么了 内格利?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.04,0:12:15.38,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell of a lot, actually. We got to talk fast{\r}\N{\rEng}其实有很多事
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.58,0:12:17.71,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,because cops are on the way to a body count{\r}\N{\rEng}我们得说快点 因为警察 正在赶来统计尸体数量的路上
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.71,0:12:19.55,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and we got to put some distance between us and them.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们得拉开距离
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.75,0:12:21.64,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything to put you at the scene?{\r}\N{\rEng}有什么能证明你们在现场的东西吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.83,0:12:23.68,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Rental car. It was shot to hell,{\r}\N{\rEng}租的车 它被射穿了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.88,0:12:25.10,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,but it was rented with Dixon's fake ID.{\r}\N{\rEng}是用迪克森的假身份证租的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.30,0:12:27.27,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We torched it to get rid of prints and DNA.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们把它烧了 以免留下指纹和DNA
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.47,0:12:29.39,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. So what happened out there?{\r}\N{\rEng}很好 所以发生了什么?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.59,0:12:32.23,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- You want the bad news or the worse news? - Surprise us.{\r}\N{\rEng}你想听坏消息 还是更坏的消息?\N让我们大吃一惊吧
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.43,0:12:35.92,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, a New Age truck with all 650 missiles in it was hijacked.{\r}\N{\rEng}一辆新时代的卡车 连同其运载的650枚导弹全被劫持了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.58,0:12:39.11,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope that's the worse news.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 希望那是更坏的消息 - 恐怕不能如你所愿
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.31,0:12:41.70,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You wish. Tony Swan's alive.{\r}\N{\rEng}托尼斯旺还活着
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.90,0:12:43.32,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- So that's a good thing. - No.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 所以那是好消息啊 - 不是
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.52,0:12:45.58,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like Swan's still working with New Age.{\r}\N{\rEng}看起来斯旺还在替新时代做事
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.78,0:12:46.83,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the bill of lading{\r}\N{\rEng}提货单上显示
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.03,0:12:48.50,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Swan personally signed off on the shipment{\r}\N{\rEng}是斯旺签字授权送货
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.70,0:12:49.79,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- before it left the factory.{\r}\N{\rEng}然后货物才离开工厂的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.99,0:12:50.87,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- So he's in Denver?{\r}\N{\rEng}那他在丹佛?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.07,0:12:53.04,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the paperwork said he authorized it from New York.{\r}\N{\rEng}文件上显示他是从纽约授权的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.24,0:12:54.71,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,So they forged his signature.{\r}\N{\rEng}所以他们伪造了他的签名?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.91,0:12:57.46,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- It's a digital thumbprint. - Then they forced him.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 是数字指纹 - 那就是他们强迫了他
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.66,0:12:59.38,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,New Age New York has iris scanners on the doors,{\r}\N{\rEng}新时代纽约分部的门上有虹膜扫描仪
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.58,0:13:01.34,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,thumbprint locks on the computers.{\r}\N{\rEng}计算机是用的指纹锁
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.54,0:13:03.84,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way that anyone could force Tony Swan{\r}\N{\rEng}任何人都无法强迫托尼斯旺
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.00,0:13:07.39,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,through that maze of biometrics without causing a huge scene.{\r}\N{\rEng}通过复杂的生物识别技术 而不引起骚乱
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.59,0:13:08.97,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,The only way they wouldn't worry about a ruckus{\r}\N{\rEng}只有一个办法能让他们不担心骚乱
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.17,0:13:10.81,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,is if all thousand-plus employees{\r}\N{\rEng}那就是让所有一千多名员工
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.01,0:13:12.02,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,were in on this thing{\r}\N{\rEng}全都参与此事
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.22,0:13:13.52,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and the odds of a conspiracy{\r}\N{\rEng}但这么大规模的阴谋的几率…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.72,0:13:15.44,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- that vast are... - Minimal.{\r}\N{\rEng}微乎其微
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.35,0:13:20.65,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you want to believe Swan's clean, boss, we all do{\r}\N{\rEng}我知道你想相信斯旺是清白的 老大 我们都想相信
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.85,0:13:22.61,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,but things look the way they look.{\r}\N{\rEng}但就目前的情况看来不是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.81,0:13:24.59,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk when we're safe, okay?{\r}\N{\rEng}等我们安全了再聊 好吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.63,0:13:27.30,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Reacher?{\r}\N{\rEng}雷彻?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.64,0:13:32.37,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Copy that.{\r}\N{\rEng}收到
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.57,0:13:34.81,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,So what you said about killing them all...{\r}\N{\rEng}你之前说要把他们都杀了
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.89,0:13:37.35,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,...that include Tony Swan?{\r}\N{\rEng}那包括托尼斯旺吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.15,0:13:43.78,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going for a walk.{\r}\N{\rEng}我要去散步
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.70,0:13:56.56,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You boys won't be needing these.{\r}\N{\rEng}你们不需要这些
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.76,0:13:59.87,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we're all friends here.{\r}\N{\rEng}是啊 我们这儿都是朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.13,0:14:03.95,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,[Franz] Took their guns.{\r}\N{\rEng}拿走了他们的枪
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.15,0:14:05.53,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Long as they didn't find the wire Swan's wearing{\r}\N{\rEng}只要他们找不到斯旺身上的窃听器
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.73,0:14:07.16,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,we're five by five.{\r}\N{\rEng}就一切安好
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.36,0:14:10.47,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Like that miscreant said, "We're all friends here."{\r}\N{\rEng}就像那个恶棍说的\N“我们这儿都是朋友”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.64,0:14:13.16,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see what you got, G.I. Joe.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 我们看看你有什么 美国兵 - 美国兵?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.36,0:14:15.50,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,G.I. Joe? More like Mighty Joe Young.{\r}\N{\rEng}说山地大猩猩更贴切吧
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.70,0:14:16.88,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,How'd you like to be jammed into a foxhole{\r}\N{\rEng}你想不想和这个大块头
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.08,0:14:18.59,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,with this giant motherfucker?{\r}\N{\rEng}挤在一个散兵坑里?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.79,0:14:20.71,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,-  We'll beat whatever price you're paying now.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们的价格比你们现在付的更优惠
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.91,0:14:22.34,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Our supplier can get you all the H you can move{\r}\N{\rEng}我们的供应商可以从
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.54,0:14:23.76,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,from an overseas source{\r}\N{\rEng}无法谈判的海外源头
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.96,0:14:25.84,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,that's in no position to negotiate terms.{\r}\N{\rEng}给你们弄来 所有你们可以转运的海洛因
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.04,0:14:28.57,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We pass the savings on to you.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们把省下来的钱都给你们
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.46,0:14:46.36,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.{\r}\N{\rEng}好的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.50,0:14:47.57,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Let's talk money. - Soon as they agree to a deal, we go.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们来谈谈价钱
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.77,0:14:49.70,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Bust them, lean on them{\r}\N{\rEng}他们一达成协议 我们就出动
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.90,0:14:52.33,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,they give up their source; we bust them{\r}\N{\rEng}逮捕他们 逼迫他们 他们会说出他们的货源
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.53,0:14:54.29,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,then we all get bumped.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们逮捕他们 然后全都能升职
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.45,0:14:55.71,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,More fruit salad on our chests...{\r}\N{\rEng}胸前的绶带和奖章就更多了
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.91,0:14:57.93,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,More dollar signs on our paychecks, bro.{\r}\N{\rEng}薪水支票上还会有 更多美元标志哦 兄弟
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.78,0:15:01.00,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would they add dollar signs to our paychecks?{\r}\N{\rEng}为什么要在我们的薪水支票上 加美元标志?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.20,0:15:02.17,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Shut up, Franzy. - The kid's got a point, Manuel.{\r}\N{\rEng}闭嘴 弗朗茨
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.37,0:15:05.55,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You only need one dollar sign.{\r}\N{\rEng}这孩子说得有道理 曼努埃尔 一个美元标志就够了 重点是零
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.65,0:15:08.65,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Assholes. - Heads up.We got incoming.{\r}\N{\rEng}混蛋 小心 有人靠近
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.25,0:15:27.09,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,About time.{\r}\N{\rEng}早该来了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.22,0:15:31.66,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,110?{\r}\N{\rEng}110?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.86,0:15:33.41,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You said you could beat our current price.{\r}\N{\rEng}你之前说价格会优于我们目前的价格
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.61,0:15:34.47,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- I am beating it.{\r}\N{\rEng}我给你们优惠了啊
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.72,0:15:36.50,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Not by enough.{\r}\N{\rEng}还不够
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.70,0:15:38.50,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You want us to change suppliers, motivate us.{\r}\N{\rEng}你想让我们更换供应商 那就打动我们吧
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.70,0:15:39.71,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,This is chicken. I said pork.{\r}\N{\rEng}鸡肉?我说的是猪肉
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.91,0:15:41.13,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- You heard me order it. - Okay.{\r}\N{\rEng}你听到我说的了。-好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.33,0:15:42.21,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Fucking idiots always get it wrong.{\r}\N{\rEng}白痴总是搞错
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.41,0:15:43.46,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,How's 105?{\r}\N{\rEng}105怎么样?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.66,0:15:45.59,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like you're wasting my fucking time.{\r}\N{\rEng}听起来像是在浪费我的时间
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.79,0:15:46.80,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- You got forks? -  You have another brick{\r}\N{\rEng}你还找得到这么纯卖105的吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.00,0:15:49.18,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- as pure as that for 105? - Seen better.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 我见过更好的 - 胡说
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.38,0:15:50.93,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Bullshit. I got a list of other buyers{\r}\N{\rEng}我有一长串买家的名单
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.13,0:15:53.18,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- a mile long. I came to you... - I know you.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 我来找你是因为你的量… - 我认识你
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.38,0:15:54.56,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,...because you purchase at a volume{\r}\N{\rEng}- …值得我花时间协商
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.76,0:15:55.56,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- which makes it worthwhile. - I don't think so.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 你认错人了吧
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.76,0:15:56.60,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I do.{\r}\N{\rEng}没认错
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.80,0:15:57.77,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Where do I know you from?{\r}\N{\rEng}我从哪儿认识你的来着?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.97,0:15:59.06,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hold on.{\r}\N{\rEng}糟了 等等
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.26,0:16:01.56,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Might be nothing. - No idea.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 可能没什么 -不知道
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.76,0:16:02.90,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,-  Look, I have other offers coming in. - I know we've met before.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 我知道我们以前见过
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.10,0:16:05.57,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,What can you do for me?{\r}\N{\rEng}- 你能为我做什么?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.77,0:16:08.03,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,100. Take it or leave it.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 一百 要么接受 要么就算了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.23,0:16:10.59,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I got it. You're the guy I sold my guitar to a while back.{\r}\N{\rEng}你是前不久买我吉他的那个人
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.88,0:16:16.79,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You got me mixed up with somebody else.{\r}\N{\rEng}你把我跟其他人搞混了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.99,0:16:18.66,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Craigslist, dude.{\r}\N{\rEng}克雷格列表网 兄弟
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.86,0:16:20.14,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You bought my acoustic.{\r}\N{\rEng}你买了我的原声吉他
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.31,0:16:25.80,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We gonna eat and discuss old times{\r}\N{\rEng}我们是要吃饭叙旧
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.00,0:16:27.42,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,or are we gonna make a deal?{\r}\N{\rEng}还是达成协议?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.62,0:16:28.72,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You assholes don't want this stuff{\r}\N{\rEng}你们这些混蛋不想要这些东西
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.92,0:16:30.11,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,we got other places we can sell it.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们有其他地方可以卖
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.86,0:16:33.72,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.{\r}\N{\rEng}等等
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.92,0:16:36.26,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute, when this guy bought it{\r}\N{\rEng}等等 这家伙买吉他的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.46,0:16:38.58,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,he was in an Army cop uniform.{\r}\N{\rEng}他穿着宪兵的制服
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.46,0:16:52.57,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck.{\r}\N{\rEng}妈的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.71,0:16:53.67,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Go, go, go, go.{\r}\N{\rEng}上!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.76,0:16:57.59,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Look out!{\r}\N{\rEng}小心!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.39,0:17:05.96,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Call an ambulance! - Don't shoot!{\r}\N{\rEng}- 叫救护车! - 别开枪
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.16,0:17:07.63,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- We have an officer down.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们有一名军官倒下了 需要医疗救援
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.83,0:17:10.09,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- We need medical assistance. - The bullet missed your heart.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 子弹没打中你的心脏
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.29,0:17:13.05,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,But shattered my collarbone.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 但打碎了我的锁骨
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.25,0:17:14.89,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Not gonna be playing that guitar for a while.{\r}\N{\rEng}我有段时间弹不了吉他了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.09,0:17:18.68,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Every cloud...  Fuck you.{\r}\N{\rEng}塞翁失马\N去你的
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.88,0:17:21.58,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hey, who don't you mess with? - The Teamsters?{\r}\N{\rEng}嘿 你不能招惹谁?\N卡车驾驶员工会?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.29,0:17:28.12,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I owe you one.{\r}\N{\rEng}我欠你一个人情
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.18,0:17:46.46,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me guess.{\r}\N{\rEng}让我猜猜
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.66,0:17:48.25,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Government plates, government suits{\r}\N{\rEng}政府牌照、政府制服
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.45,0:17:50.09,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,government rides.{\r}\N{\rEng}政府的车
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.29,0:17:51.80,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Surprised it took Senator Lavoy this long{\r}\N{\rEng}没想到拉沃伊议员花了这么长时间
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.00,0:17:54.05,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,to figure out who sweated his flunky last night.{\r}\N{\rEng}才查出昨晚是谁动了他的走狗
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.25,0:17:57.01,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,The senator has a proposition for you. Get in.{\r}\N{\rEng}参议员有个提议给你 上车
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.21,0:17:58.93,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,No.{\r}\N{\rEng}不
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.13,0:18:00.77,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Why not, Mr. Reacher?{\r}\N{\rEng}为什么 雷彻先生?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.97,0:18:02.89,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Just "Reacher."{\r}\N{\rEng}叫我雷彻
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.09,0:18:06.31,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, Reacher. Why won't you get in the car?{\r}\N{\rEng}好吧 雷彻 你为什么不上车?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.51,0:18:08.23,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he didn't ask nicely.{\r}\N{\rEng}因为他语气不善
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.43,0:18:09.90,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.{\r}\N{\rEng}好的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.10,0:18:12.71,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Hart, what's the magic word?{\r}\N{\rEng}哈特 那个神奇的词是什么?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.80,0:18:17.80,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Please get in the vehicle?{\r}\N{\rEng}请你上车?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.44,0:18:35.09,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,My man in Denver barely got away with the merchandise.{\r}\N{\rEng}我在丹佛的人带着货物侥幸逃脱
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.29,0:18:37.97,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm paying a premium for a seamless transaction{\r}\N{\rEng}我为了实现无缝交易 付出了额外的代价
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.17,0:18:41.01,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and so far this has been anything but seamless.{\r}\N{\rEng}而且目前为止 这已经算不上是无缝交易了
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.21,0:18:42.43,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,If these problems persist{\r}\N{\rEng}如果这些问题持续存在
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.63,0:18:44.31,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,there may have to be a price adjustment.{\r}\N{\rEng}那可能得调整价格了
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.51,0:18:47.40,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Some of Mr. Swan's old friends are causing us problems{\r}\N{\rEng}斯旺先生的一些老朋友 给我们带来了麻烦
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.60,0:18:49.31,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's nothing we can't handle.{\r}\N{\rEng}但没什么是我们处理不了的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.51,0:18:53.11,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want the merchandise, you honor the deal.{\r}\N{\rEng}如果你想要商品 就得遵守交易
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.31,0:18:55.09,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Do what you promised and I will.{\r}\N{\rEng}做你答应做的事 而我也会如此
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.09,0:19:00.45,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Good.{\r}\N{\rEng}好的\N很好
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.65,0:19:02.08,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you now?{\r}\N{\rEng}你现在在哪里?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.28,0:19:04.83,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I am just outside...{\r}\N{\rEng}我就在外面
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.03,0:19:06.46,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, t-this can't be right.{\r}\N{\rEng}不 这不可能是真的吧
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.66,0:19:08.63,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,"French Lick"?{\r}\N{\rEng}“弗伦奇利克”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.82,0:19:11.71,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Fucking Americans. - Indiana.{\r}\N{\rEng}他妈的美国人 印第安纳州
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.91,0:19:14.13,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.{\r}\N{\rEng}好的
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.33,0:19:15.97,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,The Little Wing chips will be ready to install{\r}\N{\rEng}等你到达这里时 小翅膀的芯片
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.17,0:19:18.30,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,in the missiles by the time you get here.{\r}\N{\rEng}会准备好安装在导弹里
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.50,0:19:21.30,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,And Mr. Swan's associates will be taken care of.{\r}\N{\rEng}斯旺先生的同事们也会处理好的
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.50,0:19:24.07,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- That plan's already in motion.{\r}\N{\rEng}计划已经开始实施了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.08,0:19:29.46,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck your king. Prick.{\r}\N{\rEng}去他妈的英国佬\N蠢货
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.64,0:19:32.87,Mark,,0000,0000,0000,,华盛顿特区史密森国家动物园
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.19,0:19:41.24,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Backstage at the primate exhibit?{\r}\N{\rEng}在灵长类动物展示区的后面
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.44,0:19:42.83,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Dramatic.{\r}\N{\rEng}够夸张的
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.03,0:19:45.51,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Thought you might feel comfortable among the gorillas.{\r}\N{\rEng}我以为你们在大猩猩中间会很舒服
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.93,0:19:49.12,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Reacher, I'm Malcolm Lavoy.{\r}\N{\rEng}雷彻先生 我是马尔科姆拉沃伊
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.32,0:19:52.09,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- He prefers just "Reacher." - No.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 他更喜欢你叫他“雷彻” - 不
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.28,0:19:53.67,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,He has to call me "Mister."{\r}\N{\rEng}他必须叫我“先生”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.87,0:19:55.38,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies for the manner in which{\r}\N{\rEng}雷彻先生 很抱歉我让人
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.58,0:19:58.26,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,you were brought in here, Mr. Reacher.{\r}\N{\rEng}用这种方式把你带过来
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.46,0:20:00.43,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Assume you use this location 'cause it's one{\r}\N{\rEng}我猜你使用这个地方 是因为这是华盛顿特区为数不多的
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.63,0:20:02.26,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,of the few spots in D.C. where you can meet{\r}\N{\rEng}你可以在没有人监视
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.46,0:20:04.31,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,without prying eyes or surveillance bugs.{\r}\N{\rEng}或窥探的情况下见面的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.51,0:20:07.39,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hmm. It's why I got myself appointed to the zoo's board.{\r}\N{\rEng}这就是为什么我任命 自己为动物园董事会成员
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.59,0:20:09.69,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Ah, I believe you know{\r}\N{\rEng}我相信你认识
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.89,0:20:10.98,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,my legislative director, Mr. Boyd.{\r}\N{\rEng}我的立法主任 博伊德先生吧?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.18,0:20:14.82,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he's the one who likes cocaine.{\r}\N{\rEng}是的\N就是他喜欢可卡因
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.02,0:20:16.90,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, when I found out what happened{\r}\N{\rEng}我知道发生了什么后
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.10,0:20:19.40,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I reached out to a friend of mine at the Bureau.{\r}\N{\rEng}我联系了我在局里的一个朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.60,0:20:21.32,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Imagine Boyd's embarrassment when he learned{\r}\N{\rEng}想象一下博伊德知道
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.52,0:20:24.91,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,that the people he revealed our secrets to{\r}\N{\rEng}自己一开始把我们的秘密透露给了
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.11,0:20:26.83,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,weren't FBI agents in the first place.{\r}\N{\rEng}非联邦特工有多尴尬
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.03,0:20:30.79,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Security video showed you entering the precinct{\r}\N{\rEng}监控录像显示你们进入了辖区
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.99,0:20:35.05,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and facial recognition software matched you to a military ID.{\r}\N{\rEng}面部识别软件 将你和一个军人的身份证相匹配
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.16,0:20:37.13,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Jack Reacher. No middle name.{\r}\N{\rEng}杰克雷彻
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.33,0:20:41.01,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,West Point, two Silver Stars{\r}\N{\rEng}没有中间名 西点军校出身 两枚银星
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.21,0:20:43.51,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,a Bronze Star, Purple Heart and so on.{\r}\N{\rEng}一枚铜星、一枚紫心勋章等等
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.71,0:20:45.28,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Show some respect.{\r}\N{\rEng}放尊重点
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.32,0:20:47.72,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,That is quite a list, and I want to thank you{\r}\N{\rEng}很多勋章啊 顺便说一句
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.92,0:20:49.73,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,for your service, by the way.{\r}\N{\rEng}感谢你的服役
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.93,0:20:51.14,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like after you retired{\r}\N{\rEng}你退役后
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.34,0:20:53.06,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,you kind of fell off the face of the Earth.{\r}\N{\rEng}像是从人间蒸发了一样
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.26,0:20:55.90,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Except for this incident a couple years ago{\r}\N{\rEng}除了几年前 在佐治亚州马格雷夫
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.10,0:20:57.32,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,in Margrave, Georgia.{\r}\N{\rEng}的一起事件
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.52,0:21:00.74,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Charged with the murder of your own brother.{\r}\N{\rEng}你被指控杀了自己的兄弟
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.94,0:21:03.20,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You were, of course, exonerated.{\r}\N{\rEng}你当然被无罪释放了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.40,0:21:06.33,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Then a massive counterfeiting operation{\r}\N{\rEng}然后 乔之前一直在调查的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.53,0:21:08.20,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,that Joe had been investigating{\r}\N{\rEng}一个大规模伪造行动
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.40,0:21:11.37,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,literally and figuratively burned to the ground.{\r}\N{\rEng}实实在在地被烧毁了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.57,0:21:13.08,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the official story was{\r}\N{\rEng}现在 官方的说辞是
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.28,0:21:15.54,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,that it was all the work of a rookie cop{\r}\N{\rEng}那都是一个菜鸟警察
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.74,0:21:17.55,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and an out-of-town veteran.{\r}\N{\rEng}和一个外地退伍军人干的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.75,0:21:19.38,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,The same out-of-town veteran{\r}\N{\rEng}也就是在波士顿逮捕了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.58,0:21:21.30,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,that arrested Boyd here in Boston.{\r}\N{\rEng}博伊德的这位外地退伍军人
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.50,0:21:22.84,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Get to the point.{\r}\N{\rEng}说重点吧
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.04,0:21:25.35,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Smells like monkey shit in here.{\r}\N{\rEng}这里有股猴子屎的味道
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.54,0:21:28.74,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I know it was you in Margrave, Mr. Reacher.{\r}\N{\rEng}雷彻先生 我知道马格雷夫的事 是你做的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.34,0:21:32.49,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to do the same thing for the situation we have here.{\r}\N{\rEng}我希望针对我们目前的情况 你也能做同样的事
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.88,0:21:42.32,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Why? - Because in Boston, you insinuated to Boyd{\r}\N{\rEng}为什么?\N因为在波士顿 你暗示博伊德
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.52,0:21:44.32,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,that military and civilian aircraft{\r}\N{\rEng}军队和民用飞机
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.52,0:21:46.20,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,could be in danger due to Little Wing.{\r}\N{\rEng}可能会因为小翅膀而陷入危险
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.40,0:21:48.08,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I can only assume that means that terrorists{\r}\N{\rEng}现在 我只能假设那意味着\N恐怖分子对这项技术很感兴趣
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.28,0:21:51.00,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,are interested in the tech, working hard to obtain it.{\r}\N{\rEng}正在努力获得它
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.20,0:21:53.54,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,See, once we identified you, we looked into things deeper{\r}\N{\rEng}一旦我们确认了你的身份 我们就深入调查
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.74,0:21:55.88,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and we learned that your old unit's back together{\r}\N{\rEng}我们知道你以前的小队又重组了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.08,0:21:58.34,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and some are dead.{\r}\N{\rEng}其中有些人死了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.54,0:22:00.30,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look so shocked, Mr. Reacher{\r}\N{\rEng}别那么震惊 雷彻先生
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.50,0:22:02.59,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a U.S. congressman, I get things done.{\r}\N{\rEng}我是美国国会议员 我能把事情做好
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.79,0:22:05.93,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm shocked because a U.S. congressman got anything done.{\r}\N{\rEng}我很震惊 是因为 美国国会议员居然还能做事
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.46,0:22:10.74,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm used to the slings and arrows, Mr. Reacher.{\r}\N{\rEng}我已经习惯了 人们的阴阳怪气 雷彻先生
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.82,0:22:15.60,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,But bottom line the people who want this weaponry{\r}\N{\rEng}我的底线是想要这个武器的人
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.80,0:22:17.15,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,can never be allowed to have it.{\r}\N{\rEng}绝对不能被允许持有该武器
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.35,0:22:18.77,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Because if anyone knew{\r}\N{\rEng}因为如果有人知道
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.97,0:22:20.32,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,you were involved in the shady dealings{\r}\N{\rEng}你从一开始就参与了
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.52,0:22:22.65,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,that created Little Wing in the first place{\r}\N{\rEng}创造小翅膀的不正当交易
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.85,0:22:24.07,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,you'd be indicted.{\r}\N{\rEng}你就会被起诉
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.27,0:22:26.41,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Get rid of the bad guys, keep my hands clean.{\r}\N{\rEng}除掉坏人 让我干干净净的
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.61,0:22:28.38,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,In Washington, we call that a win-win.{\r}\N{\rEng}在华盛顿 我们称之为双赢
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.43,0:22:32.58,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I did what I did to give our side the tools they need{\r}\N{\rEng}我尽我所能 给予了我方捍卫民主
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.78,0:22:34.50,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,to defend democracy.{\r}\N{\rEng}所需的工具
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.70,0:22:37.00,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I just avoided the typical red tape that does nothing{\r}\N{\rEng}我只是避免了繁文缛节 那些没什么用 只会拖延时间
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.20,0:22:39.63,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,but cause the delays that cost lives.{\r}\N{\rEng}造成生命损失
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.83,0:22:41.59,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,And lined your pockets in the process.{\r}\N{\rEng}还在这个过程中中饱私囊
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.79,0:22:44.55,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Again, win-win.{\r}\N{\rEng}再次重申 这叫双赢
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.75,0:22:47.26,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't want innocent people to die because of it.{\r}\N{\rEng}我不想让无辜群众因为这种武器而死
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.46,0:22:50.35,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a political animal, I'm not a monster, Mr. Reacher.{\r}\N{\rEng}我是政客 不是怪物 雷彻先生
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.55,0:22:53.22,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm not asking for your help{\r}\N{\rEng}而且我不是请你帮忙
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.42,0:22:55.14,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm offering you mine.{\r}\N{\rEng}我是给你提供帮助
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.34,0:22:57.73,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the kind of man who likes to gets things done, too.{\r}\N{\rEng}你也是那种喜欢把事情做好的人
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.93,0:23:00.40,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Your record in the military, and in Margrave, proves that.{\r}\N{\rEng}你在军队和马格雷夫的记录 证明了这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.60,0:23:02.44,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You like to upset the apple cart.{\r}\N{\rEng}你喜欢打乱计划
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.64,0:23:04.65,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm prepared to give you whatever you need{\r}\N{\rEng}我准备给予你所需要的一切
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.85,0:23:07.16,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,to aid you in that endeavor.{\r}\N{\rEng}协助你完成这项任务
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.35,0:23:09.16,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,And when you're done{\r}\N{\rEng}等你完工后
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.36,0:23:11.16,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,no one will be able to prove that you were ever near{\r}\N{\rEng}没有人能证明你
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.36,0:23:12.97,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,those apples in the first place.{\r}\N{\rEng}曾卷入过那些计划
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.60,0:23:17.37,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Just smash this thing to bits. Leave no man left standing.{\r}\N{\rEng}就把这些东西砸成碎片 把这些人全都一网打尽
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.57,0:23:20.00,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,No one left to endanger lives.{\r}\N{\rEng}不遗留任何人威胁他人生命
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:22.75,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,And then you can disappear again.{\r}\N{\rEng}然后你就又可以消失了
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.95,0:23:24.96,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,No one will go looking for you.{\r}\N{\rEng}没有人会继续找你
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.16,0:23:26.94,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Or your friends.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们是你的朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.23,0:23:54.24,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?{\r}\N{\rEng}怎么?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.44,0:23:56.62,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Not-So-Jolly Green Giant.{\r}\N{\rEng}嘿 不怎么快乐的巨人
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.82,0:23:57.96,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- You throw away that suit yet? - No. Why?{\r}\N{\rEng}你已经把那套衣服扔了吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.16,0:23:59.46,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Coroner finally released Franz's body.{\r}\N{\rEng}没有 怎么了?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.66,0:24:01.21,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,验尸官终于归还了弗朗茨的尸体
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.41,0:24:02.44,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Funeral's tomorrow.{\r}\N{\rEng}葬礼在明天举行
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.41,0:24:05.19,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We got to go back to New York.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们得回纽约
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.53,0:24:16.47,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Had my office make some discrete inquiries.{\r}\N{\rEng}葬礼
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.67,0:24:19.19,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Denver sheriffs found the shot-up truck{\r}\N{\rEng}我让我的办公室做了一些零星的调查
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.39,0:24:22.06,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,with a switched-out trailer.Nothing in it but crates of bricks.{\r}\N{\rEng}丹佛的警察发现了 被枪击的卡车和被掉包的拖车
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.26,0:24:24.69,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Guessing they perfectly matched the weight{\r}\N{\rEng}- 里面什么都没有 只有几块砖 - 它们完美匹配
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.85,0:24:25.86,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,of the launchers and the missiles.{\r}\N{\rEng}发射器和导弹的重量?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.06,0:24:27.86,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. It seems their plan{\r}\N{\rEng}是的 看来他们的计划 是开车将假的货物
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.06,0:24:29.57,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,was to drive the dummy cargo down to the port{\r}\N{\rEng}运送到洛杉矶港口
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.77,0:24:31.24,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- in L.A. - And ship it to an Army base{\r}\N{\rEng}然后送到菲律宾的军事基地
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.44,0:24:34.87,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,in the Philippines or wherever the weapons were supposed to go.{\r}\N{\rEng}或者任何那武器应该去的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.07,0:24:37.29,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,South Korea, according to the documents we saw.{\r}\N{\rEng}根据我们的资料显示 是韩国
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.49,0:24:38.79,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Smart.{\r}\N{\rEng}真聪明
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.99,0:24:40.83,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Three to four weeks for a cargo ship to get there{\r}\N{\rEng}货船从西海岸到那里 需要三到四周的时间
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.03,0:24:43.50,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,from the West Coast, no one knows the weapons were missing{\r}\N{\rEng}在另一边开箱前
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.70,0:24:45.21,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,till they open it up on the other end.{\r}\N{\rEng}没人知道武器失踪了
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.41,0:24:46.92,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,And who knows how long that could be?{\r}\N{\rEng}谁知道那要多长时间呢?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.12,0:24:48.34,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Army could just load it into storage{\r}\N{\rEng}军队可能会直接将其放到仓库
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.54,0:24:49.59,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and not see them again for months.{\r}\N{\rEng}几个月都不看它们
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.79,0:24:51.47,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,And by then, it's too late.{\r}\N{\rEng}到那时 为时已晚
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.67,0:24:53.30,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Terrorists have taken down dozens of planes{\r}\N{\rEng}恐怖分子已经击落了数十架飞机
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.50,0:24:55.43,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and we have no idea where they got the firepower.{\r}\N{\rEng}而我们还不知道 他们从哪儿弄来的武器
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.63,0:24:57.06,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of firepower, we have any leads{\r}\N{\rEng}说起武器
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.26,0:24:59.23,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,as to where the real missiles went?Colorado State Police found the truck{\r}\N{\rEng}有任何关于真正的导弹的 去向的线索吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.43,0:25:02.94,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,in a field outside Denver.- It was empty.{\r}\N{\rEng}科罗拉多州警方在丹佛外的 一块田里发现了那辆卡车 是空的
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.14,0:25:04.36,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Based on the tracks in the dirt{\r}\N{\rEng}根据卡车在泥土里的痕迹来看
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.56,0:25:07.23,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,they think a private plane flew the weapons out overnight.{\r}\N{\rEng}他们认为一架私人飞机 连夜把武器带走了
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.43,0:25:08.63,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Could be headed here.{\r}\N{\rEng}它可能会去往任何地方
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.83,0:25:11.99,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Since 9/11, they've kept a pretty close watch on New York's skies.{\r}\N{\rEng}自从911以后 纽约上空就一直受到了密切地监控
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.19,0:25:13.42,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,And we know A.M.'s cautious.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们知道AM很谨慎
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.52,0:25:16.99,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I were him, I'd fly them into some small airstrip{\r}\N{\rEng}如果我是他\N我会把它们带到 宾夕法尼亚州的某个小机场里
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.19,0:25:18.66,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,in Pennsylvania, maybe New Hampshire{\r}\N{\rEng}也可以是新罕布什尔州 再开车将武器运到纽约
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.86,0:25:20.41,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,then drive the weapons into New York to load them up{\r}\N{\rEng}好给它们加上小翅膀软件
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.61,0:25:22.83,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- with the Little Wing software. - That makes sense.{\r}\N{\rEng}言之有理
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.03,0:25:24.79,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to know exactly where the missiles are headed{\r}\N{\rEng}我们需要知道导弹 到底是在往哪儿运
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.99,0:25:26.50,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,so we can intercept them.{\r}\N{\rEng}才能拦截它们
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.70,0:25:28.42,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause when the money changes hands{\r}\N{\rEng}因为当钱易手时
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.62,0:25:31.86,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,A.M. will be there, and so will the people who killed our guys.{\r}\N{\rEng}AM会到场 杀了我们的人的凶手也在
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.57,0:25:41.60,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Reacher. You seeing this shit?{\r}\N{\rEng}雷彻 你看到那玩意了吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.80,0:25:43.94,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that that toy he had in his car the other day?{\r}\N{\rEng}那不是那天他车里的玩具吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.14,0:25:47.69,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikey.My nephews have the same one.{\r}\N{\rEng}米奇 我的侄子也有一个
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.89,0:25:49.86,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a great toy.{\r}\N{\rEng}这是个很棒的玩具
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.06,0:25:52.86,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We play with it all the time.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们一直一起玩
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.06,0:25:57.16,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was a kid, I had Aquaman.{\r}\N{\rEng}我小时候 我有海王
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.36,0:26:01.37,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was so cool how he could talk to fish.{\r}\N{\rEng}我觉得他跟鱼说话的方式太酷了
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.57,0:26:03.51,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause I wanted to talk to my dog, you know?{\r}\N{\rEng}因为我当时也想跟我的狗说话
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.60,0:26:11.86,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.{\r}\N{\rEng}嘿
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.86,0:26:15.76,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to have this, too.{\r}\N{\rEng}我也想把这张照片给你 这是我的
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.96,0:26:19.35,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,This was mine. Saint Jerome.{\r}\N{\rEng}圣杰罗姆
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.55,0:26:20.81,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the patron saint of kids{\r}\N{\rEng}他是爸爸或妈妈去了天堂的
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.01,0:26:23.28,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,whose moms and dads go to heaven.{\r}\N{\rEng}孩子的守护神
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.49,0:26:33.49,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to say the prayer...on the back every night.{\r}\N{\rEng}我希望你每晚都念这照片后面的祈祷词
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.69,0:26:36.05,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll help keep your dad close.{\r}\N{\rEng}它会让你爸离你近点
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.22,0:26:40.84,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you do that?{\r}\N{\rEng}你能做到吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.85,0:26:44.26,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Good boy.{\r}\N{\rEng}好孩子
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.27,0:26:47.89,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Good boy.{\r}\N{\rEng}好孩子
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.35,0:26:53.30,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You need anything, you call me.{\r}\N{\rEng}你有任何需要 就给我打电话
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.50,0:26:54.92,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Day or night.{\r}\N{\rEng}白天晚上都行
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.12,0:26:57.51,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Thank you. - Yeah.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 谢谢 - 没事
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.71,0:27:00.99,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Mikey. They're just about to start.{\r}\N{\rEng}来吧 米奇 葬礼要开始了
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.12,0:27:06.73,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you giving toys to my dead friend's son?{\r}\N{\rEng}你为什么要送玩具 给我死去的朋友的儿子?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.93,0:27:07.79,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me?{\r}\N{\rEng}什么?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.60,0:27:12.48,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Cozy up to the kid, score points with Mom.{\r}\N{\rEng}和孩子相处融洽 就能刷妈妈的好感度
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.68,0:27:16.49,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You see a grieving widow and think, "Easy target"?{\r}\N{\rEng}你看到一个悲伤的寡妇 心想：“这个目标容易得手”?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.69,0:27:18.49,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you kidding me right now?{\r}\N{\rEng}你现在在跟我开玩笑吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.69,0:27:20.87,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You got some kind of death wish?{\r}\N{\rEng}你是想找死吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.07,0:27:23.66,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Some people think so. - I'm here to pay my respects.{\r}\N{\rEng}有些人这么想\N我是来表达敬意的
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.86,0:27:26.16,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did a biker gang take a run at me in Boston last night?{\r}\N{\rEng}为什么昨晚在波士顿 有一个摩托车团伙攻击我?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.36,0:27:28.54,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- 'Cause you're an asshole. - Possibly.{\r}\N{\rEng}因为你是个混蛋 可能吧
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.74,0:27:30.29,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Or maybe it's 'cause you're the only person I told{\r}\N{\rEng}也可能是因为 我们只把
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.49,0:27:32.30,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- we were going there. - Wait, wait, wait.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们的行踪告诉了你 等等
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.49,0:27:34.67,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to say that I'm bent?{\r}\N{\rEng}你是想说我是黑警?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.87,0:27:36.77,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Not trying to say anything.{\r}\N{\rEng}我什么都没想说
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.78,0:27:40.80,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You know why I was talking to Mikey?{\r}\N{\rEng}你知道我为什么跟米奇说话吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.00,0:27:42.64,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I know what he's going through.{\r}\N{\rEng}因为我知道他在经历什么
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.84,0:27:44.85,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what it is to look out the window every night{\r}\N{\rEng}我知道每晚看着窗户外面
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.05,0:27:48.23,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and pray that the next set of headlights coming down the street is your father's car{\r}\N{\rEng}祈祷街上来的是自己父亲的车 是什么感觉
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.43,0:27:50.23,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,even though you know it'll never happen{\r}\N{\rEng}即使你知道那永远不会发生
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.43,0:27:52.69,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,because you saw the guys from Romano's funeral home{\r}\N{\rEng}因为你亲眼看到 罗马诺殡仪馆的那些家伙
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.89,0:27:54.82,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,throw dirt on his casket.{\r}\N{\rEng}在他的棺材上撒土
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.02,0:27:56.69,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what it is to lose family?{\r}\N{\rEng}你知道失去家人是什么感觉吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.89,0:27:59.53,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, they're all dead. Every one of them.{\r}\N{\rEng}是啊 他们都死了 全都死了
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.73,0:28:02.12,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,And I was talking about you, not your father.{\r}\N{\rEng}而我在说你 - 没说你爸
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.32,0:28:03.49,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about him.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 我在说他
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.69,0:28:05.87,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,My father was a cop, a good one{\r}\N{\rEng}我爸曾是一名警察 一个好警察
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.07,0:28:08.68,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and he refused to be on the take and they killed him for it.{\r}\N{\rEng}他拒绝受贿 因此被人杀害
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.35,0:28:16.51,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I know that's your friend's son and widow.{\r}\N{\rEng}听着 我知道那是 你朋友的儿子和遗孀
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.71,0:28:17.72,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it.{\r}\N{\rEng}我懂
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.92,0:28:19.43,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,But you call me dirty one more time{\r}\N{\rEng}但如果你再说我是黑警
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.63,0:28:22.76,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and I don't care if we're standing in front of the statue of the Holy Mother{\r}\N{\rEng}我不在乎我们是否是站在圣母像面前
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.96,0:28:25.93,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I will give you that beating that I owe you right here.{\r}\N{\rEng}我会新账老账一起算 就在这里狠狠揍你一顿
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.13,0:28:29.81,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,One, I'll take that fight any time you want.{\r}\N{\rEng}第一 只要你想 我随时奉陪
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.01,0:28:32.52,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,And two...{\r}\N{\rEng}第二
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.72,0:28:34.40,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know that about your father.{\r}\N{\rEng}我不知道你父亲的事
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.60,0:28:36.69,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well, what you don't know could fill the Javits.{\r}\N{\rEng}是啊 你不知道的事可多了去了
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.89,0:28:39.40,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Because while you were in Boston doing God knows what{\r}\N{\rEng}因为天知道你在波士顿做什么的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.60,0:28:42.07,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I was running those security names from New Age.{\r}\N{\rEng}我在忙着查新时代安保部的人
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.27,0:28:44.20,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,All former NYPD, all from the 3rd precinct.{\r}\N{\rEng}他们全都是前纽约市警察局的
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.40,0:28:45.79,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,The boss, Langston and a few other guys{\r}\N{\rEng}全部来自第三分局
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.98,0:28:49.58,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,they were under investigation by IA.{\r}\N{\rEng}老板兰斯顿和其他几个人 都接受过内务部的调查
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.78,0:28:52.33,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,They took early retirement and the charges went away.{\r}\N{\rEng}他们提前退休了 那些指控就消失了
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.53,0:28:54.54,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Then they all got cushy jobs at New Age{\r}\N{\rEng}然后他们全都在新时代 找到了轻松的工作
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.74,0:28:56.42,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and they hired all their pals along.{\r}\N{\rEng}雇佣了所有朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.62,0:28:57.84,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Whole team of bad cops?{\r}\N{\rEng}整个团队全是黑警?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.04,0:28:59.76,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody except your buddy Swan.{\r}\N{\rEng}所有人 除了你的朋友 斯旺
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.96,0:29:01.76,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,But he's the only one that has military experience{\r}\N{\rEng}但他是唯一一个有从军经历
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.96,0:29:04.30,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,to know what type of weapons terrorists want, so...{\r}\N{\rEng}知道恐怖分子 想要哪种武器的人 所以…
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.50,0:29:06.43,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you're implying something that's pissing me off.{\r}\N{\rEng}现在你在含沙射影地说 会让我生气的事
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.63,0:29:08.35,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't deny he makes sense for this.{\r}\N{\rEng}你不能否认这种猜想是合理的
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.55,0:29:10.85,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,With his background, for all we know{\r}\N{\rEng}根据他的背景
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.05,0:29:12.40,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,he might have put the whole thing together.{\r}\N{\rEng}这一切可能都是他主使的
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.59,0:29:15.73,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,All cops, all bad, all from the same precinct.{\r}\N{\rEng}所有警察 全是黑警 都是一个辖区的
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.93,0:29:18.48,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- You interview any of them? - Couldn't.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 你审问过他们中任何人吗? - 问不了
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.68,0:29:20.70,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You turned their office into a drive-through.{\r}\N{\rEng}你在他们办公的地方砸出了一个大洞
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.89,0:29:21.90,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,They went to the ground.{\r}\N{\rEng}他们躲起来了
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.10,0:29:25.37,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Their places were empty, just like Tony Swan's.{\r}\N{\rEng}他们的住处空无一人 跟托尼斯旺的住处一样
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.57,0:29:27.79,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to call somebody dirty?{\r}\N{\rEng}你想骂某人是黑警?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.99,0:29:29.72,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,First look in your own backyard.{\r}\N{\rEng}先查查你自己的后院吧
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.69,0:29:43.05,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We therefore commit our brother Calvin Franz to the ground{\r}\N{\rEng}因此 我们要将我们的兄弟 卡尔文弗朗茨埋葬
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.25,0:29:47.31,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,earth to earth, ashes to ashes, dust to dust{\r}\N{\rEng}归于大地 尘归尘 土归土
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.50,0:29:50.81,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,in sure and certain hope of the resurrection{\r}\N{\rEng}让往生者安宁
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.01,0:29:52.64,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,to the eternal life.{\r}\N{\rEng}让在世者重获解脱
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.84,0:29:53.99,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Amen.{\r}\N{\rEng}阿门
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.09,0:29:56.37,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Amen.{\r}\N{\rEng}阿门
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.57,0:30:25.86,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Firing party, attention.{\r}\N{\rEng}鸣枪队 注意!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.78,0:30:29.78,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Stand by.{\r}\N{\rEng}待命
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.12,0:30:33.95,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready.{\r}\N{\rEng}准备
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.66,0:30:38.58,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Aim.{\r}\N{\rEng}瞄准
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.75,0:30:40.71,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire.{\r}\N{\rEng}开火!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.38,0:30:42.50,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready.{\r}\N{\rEng}准备
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.56,0:30:46.88,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Aim.- Fire.{\r}\N{\rEng}瞄准 开火!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.13,0:30:51.49,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Get down! - Fire...{\r}\N{\rEng}- 趴下! - 开火
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.22,0:30:55.87,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I got you. Come on. Let's go.{\r}\N{\rEng}我保护你们 快 我们走
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.07,0:30:57.25,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of here. Go.{\r}\N{\rEng}离开这里 快走!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.45,0:30:59.21,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Active shooters! Run!{\r}\N{\rEng}有人开枪 快跑!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.41,0:31:01.19,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!{\r}\N{\rEng}走!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.66,0:31:15.77,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,How many?{\r}\N{\rEng}- 几个人?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.97,0:31:18.35,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,As far as I can tell, two. Across the road.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 据我所知两个 在路对面
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.55,0:31:20.23,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Handguns are useless from this distance. We got to get closer.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 手枪没用 得离近点!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.43,0:31:22.23,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Flank them. Neagley and I will take the one on the right.{\r}\N{\rEng}包抄他们 内格利和我 负责右边的那个
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.43,0:31:23.86,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You two take the one on the left.{\r}\N{\rEng}你们俩负责左边那个
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.06,0:31:25.34,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Go.{\r}\N{\rEng}上
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.69,0:31:50.22,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Close as we're gonna get. It's not enough.{\r}\N{\rEng}我们尽可能接近 还不够
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.42,0:31:51.76,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- We could wait for the cops. - We can't let them get away.{\r}\N{\rEng}可以等警察来
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.96,0:31:55.53,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as they hear sirens, they scatter.{\r}\N{\rEng}不能让他们跑了 他们一听到警笛就会散开
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.05,0:31:58.69,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.{\r}\N{\rEng}好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.89,0:32:00.52,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll draw their fire, you take them out.{\r}\N{\rEng}我来吸引火力 你去干掉他们
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.72,0:32:02.23,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Negative. -  You can do this.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 我拒绝 - 你能做到
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.43,0:32:03.94,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- You're a great shot.{\r}\N{\rEng}你射得很准
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.14,0:32:05.17,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- But you're a slow runner.{\r}\N{\rEng}但你跑得很慢
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.01,0:32:20.89,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck this.{\r}\N{\rEng}去你的 糟了!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.02,0:32:47.84,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Get in!{\r}\N{\rEng}上车!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.84,0:32:55.41,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you trust me now, or are you just desperate?{\r}\N{\rEng}你现在相信我了 还是饥不择食了?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.57,0:32:57.12,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw you protect Angela and Mikey{\r}\N{\rEng}我看见你保护安吉拉和米奇
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.32,0:32:58.97,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,so I guess you're playing it square.{\r}\N{\rEng}所以我猜你说的是真的
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.47,0:33:03.43,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You got a rat in your house, though, that's for sure.{\r}\N{\rEng}但你那儿有内鬼 那是肯定的
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.65,0:33:12.51,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Shit, Russo, it's the pedal on the right.{\r}\N{\rEng}妈的 拉索 开快点
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.71,0:33:14.15,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me do my job.{\r}\N{\rEng}让我做我的工作
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.20,0:33:20.27,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Cut the corner. - There's a curb.{\r}\N{\rEng}抄近路\N- 有路缘石 - 跳过去
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.47,0:33:23.54,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Jump the curb! - Will you climb out of my ass?{\r}\N{\rEng}你能别管我怎么开车吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.59,0:33:32.92,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought this was supposed to be a high-speed pursuit.{\r}\N{\rEng}我以为这应该是高速追逐战
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.68,0:33:42.21,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You're losing our best lead.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 我们最好的线索要被你搞丢了
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.41,0:33:44.13,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to drive?{\r}\N{\rEng}- 你想来开车吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.32,0:33:47.02,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yes. - Hey, hey.{\r}\N{\rEng}好啊\N嘿!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.17,0:34:09.65,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a fucking menace, you know that?{\r}\N{\rEng}- 你真他妈是个祸害!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.85,0:34:11.00,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You drive like you're blind.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 你开车像个瞎子一样
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.92,0:34:16.49,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't shoot. I'm done.{\r}\N{\rEng}别开枪 我受够了
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.69,0:34:19.16,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay? I'm done.{\r}\N{\rEng}好吗?我受够了
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.36,0:34:21.66,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You're under arrest, asshole.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 你被捕了 混蛋
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.86,0:34:24.17,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,No.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 不
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.31,0:34:27.50,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,These guys took a run at us in broad daylight at a crowded funeral.{\r}\N{\rEng}这些人在光天化日之下 攻击我们 还是在人多的葬礼上
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.70,0:34:30.55,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,They're getting desperate.Means this thing's coming to a head fast.{\r}\N{\rEng}他们越来越绝望了 这意味着这事快到紧要关头了
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.75,0:34:31.80,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We take him in, he lawyers up{\r}\N{\rEng}我们拘留他 他会请律师
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.00,0:34:33.42,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and doesn't talk until it's too late{\r}\N{\rEng}在为时已晚前缄口不言
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.62,0:34:34.76,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and a terrorist has 650 chances{\r}\N{\rEng}恐怖分子有650次机会
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.96,0:34:36.26,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,to take down a commercial airliner.{\r}\N{\rEng}击落一架商业客机
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.46,0:34:37.64,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do you want me to do?{\r}\N{\rEng}所以你想让我做什么?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.84,0:34:39.36,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Look the other way.{\r}\N{\rEng}看向另一边
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.91,0:34:46.25,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on, man.{\r}\N{\rEng}拜托 伙计
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.14,0:34:50.48,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,By not telling me everything you know{\r}\N{\rEng}如果你不告诉我你知道的一切
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.68,0:34:52.78,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,you're protecting the people who killed my friends.{\r}\N{\rEng}那就是在保护杀了我朋友的人
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.98,0:34:54.03,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna waste my time{\r}\N{\rEng}我不会浪费时间
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.23,0:34:55.99,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,with enhanced interrogation techniques.{\r}\N{\rEng}用那些审讯技巧
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.19,0:34:57.82,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just gonna squeeze the life out of you.{\r}\N{\rEng}我只会夺走你的生命
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.02,0:34:59.91,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,So, if at any point before you die{\r}\N{\rEng}如果你在你死前
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.11,0:35:03.20,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,you feel like fully unburdening yourself...{\r}\N{\rEng}想完全卸下自己的负担
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.40,0:35:04.89,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,blink.{\r}\N{\rEng}那就眨眼
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.52,0:35:13.51,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Talk, now. - Okay.{\r}\N{\rEng}- 现在说话 - 好的
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.71,0:35:15.22,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Christ.{\r}\N{\rEng}天啊
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.42,0:35:17.09,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me catch my breath.{\r}\N{\rEng}让我喘口气
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.45,0:35:22.93,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We were supposed to use the gunfire{\r}\N{\rEng}我们本来应该利用21响礼炮的枪声
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.13,0:35:25.81,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,from the 21-gun salute to mask our shot.{\r}\N{\rEng}来掩盖我们的射击
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.01,0:35:27.27,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Take you and your team down and get out of there{\r}\N{\rEng}干掉你和你的团队成员
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.47,0:35:29.52,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,before anyone knew what was going on.\NEasy payday for a couple professional hitters.{\r}\N{\rEng}在任何人搞清楚状况前离开
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.72,0:35:31.48,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,对于专业枪手来说 赚这钱轻松容易
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.68,0:35:33.73,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Tell me something I don't know. - Like what?{\r}\N{\rEng}- 跟我说些我不知道的事 - 比如?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.93,0:35:35.40,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Langston wouldn't give you all the cash up front.{\r}\N{\rEng}兰斯顿不会一开始就把所有钱都给你
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.60,0:35:37.82,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you supposed to meet him to get the rest of the money?{\r}\N{\rEng}你要在哪里见他拿尾款?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.02,0:35:39.41,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,An abandoned building{\r}\N{\rEng}皇后区某个破烂街区的
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.61,0:35:41.41,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,in some shitty neighborhood in Queens.{\r}\N{\rEng}一栋废弃建筑里
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.61,0:35:43.87,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I-I can take you there.{\r}\N{\rEng}我可以带你们去
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.07,0:35:45.83,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't know any Langston.{\r}\N{\rEng}但我不认识兰斯顿
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.03,0:35:47.79,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who hired you?{\r}\N{\rEng}那是谁雇的你?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.99,0:35:49.68,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Some guy called Swan.{\r}\N{\rEng}一个叫斯旺的家伙
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.23,0:36:00.51,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Copy that.{\r}\N{\rEng}收到
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.71,0:36:02.35,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Dixon and O'Donnell are in position.{\r}\N{\rEng}迪克森和奥唐纳已就位
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.55,0:36:03.89,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Russo's down the street.{\r}\N{\rEng}拉索在街上
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.09,0:36:06.27,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- All exits are covered. - Hear that?{\r}\N{\rEng}所有出口都已覆盖 听到了吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.47,0:36:08.39,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You try anything, you'll be sorry.{\r}\N{\rEng}你要是敢乱来 你会后悔的
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.59,0:36:10.81,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,But you go in there, get paid, give us the rundown...{\r}\N{\rEng}你进去拿钱 给我们这地方的信息
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.01,0:36:12.90,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,How many inside, what they're packing...{\r}\N{\rEng}里面有多少人 他们带着什么武器
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.10,0:36:15.23,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Layout of the room, where everyone's sitting...{\r}\N{\rEng}房间的布局 人都坐在哪里
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.43,0:36:17.44,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll cut you loose and you get to keep the cash.{\r}\N{\rEng}然后我们就放了你 你可以留着钱 懂了吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.64,0:36:20.66,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- Understood? - Yeah, man. Whatever.{\r}\N{\rEng}好的 随便吧
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.86,0:36:24.24,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I just never want to see you people again.{\r}\N{\rEng}我只希望永远都不会再见到你们
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.44,0:36:26.39,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me your phone.{\r}\N{\rEng}把你的手机给我
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.06,0:36:35.67,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep this in your pocket so we can listen in.{\r}\N{\rEng}把这个放在口袋里 这样我们就能监听
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.87,0:36:37.30,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,You try anything, we come in hot{\r}\N{\rEng}你要是敢做小动作 我们会突然进攻
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.50,0:36:40.01,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,and you die with the rest of them.{\r}\N{\rEng}你就跟他们一起死吧
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.21,0:36:42.15,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Get going, stupid.{\r}\N{\rEng}去吧 蠢货
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.16,0:36:52.02,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what are we thinking?{\r}\N{\rEng}我们在想什么?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.22,0:36:54.06,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Swan went to work for New Age{\r}\N{\rEng}斯旺去新时代工作
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.26,0:36:55.48,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,saw a chance to make the kind of money{\r}\N{\rEng}看到了他一直梦寐以求的赚钱机会
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.68,0:36:57.40,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,he always dreamed of and took it?{\r}\N{\rEng}然后就接受了?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.60,0:36:59.65,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what? He was hanging out with Franzy{\r}\N{\rEng}然后呢?他跟弗朗茨一起出去玩
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.85,0:37:01.57,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,them being in the same city and all{\r}\N{\rEng}他们都在一个城市
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.77,0:37:04.42,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,slipped and said something that made Franz suspicious?{\r}\N{\rEng}不小心透露了什么 让弗朗茨产生了怀疑
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.53,0:37:08.91,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Or...tried to get Franz in on it?{\r}\N{\rEng}或者他试着拉弗朗茨入伙
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.11,0:37:11.54,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Figured with a wife and kid, he'd need the money, too.{\r}\N{\rEng}心想要养老婆和孩子 他也需要钱
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.74,0:37:14.29,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,Franz said no, tried to stop it{\r}\N{\rEng}弗朗茨拒绝了 试图阻止
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.49,0:37:16.38,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,called Sanchez and Orozco for help.{\r}\N{\rEng}打电话给 桑切斯和奥罗斯科求助
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.58,0:37:18.01,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,That sound about right?{\r}\N{\rEng}那听起来对吗?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.20,0:37:20.59,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,- I don't know{\r}\N{\rEng}我不知道
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.79,0:37:22.01,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,but if Swan's really in that building{\r}\N{\rEng}但如果斯旺真在那栋楼里
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.21,0:37:24.01,Ch,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna do the same thing I did to that guy.{\r}\N{\rEng}我也会像对待那家伙一样对待斯旺
